laboratory_examinations.findings: Abdomen shows bibasilar atelectasis, no pleural effusion or pneumothorax, normal in size heart, no pericardial effusion, liver enhances homogeneously without focal lesions, normal gallbladder, no intrahepatic biliary ductal dilation, normal spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands, kidneys enhance symmetrically, no hydronephrosis or retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy, no free air or fluid, normal stomach and small bowel, unremarkable aorta and its branches, patent portal vein, splenic vein and superior mesenteric vein. Pelvis shows dilated and thickened appendix measuring 1 cm with adjacent fat stranding, thickening of the lateral conal fascia, no adjacent fluid collection or evidence of perforation, mildly prominent likely reactive adjacent lymph nodes, unremarkable remainder of the colon, normal bladder, prostate, and sigmoid, no free pelvic fluid. No suspicious osseous lesions.
